    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-11T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-11T05:00:00-05:00" n="821"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d821">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3401</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-11T10:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.46 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6218. Following joint telegram from Allied Ministers at Jassy, dated Army of the
                    Danube, December 7: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>[845.] The Russian delegation having brought to our notice the immediate
                            necessity of a denunciatory declaration to the Bolsheviks we have
                            charged the French Consul at Kiev to make it in our name. We did not
                            hesitate to do this so as to prepare, as far as possible, the channels
                            for an intervention on the part of the Allies; although the decisions of
                            the Entente in this regard have not yet been notified to us. We send in
                            our telegram in plain language No. 846<note n="1" xml:id="d821fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                            </note> the text of this declaration. The first part was drafted at
                            Jassy, the second part to the present government of Kiev was added there
                            by the French Consul. Exercising the latitude which we had given him he
                            considered, in view of the local situation, that without making
                            engagements any time for the future the present system of government
                            should be supported as it represented the only organization which could
                            at present be utilized against Bolshevism.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
